# Configuring WireGuard 
Now first what you will have to do is download wireguard on your device then head into your ssh.
Once your in your ssh enter these code to install it into your webserver.
sudo apt update
sudo apt install wireguard -y
Now to verify you installation enter this code
wg --version
# The VPN server keys
With WireGuard your going to have the keys they generate for them to work to get them your going to have to navigate to the wireguard directory:
Enter these code
cd /etc/wireguard
Now to generate the private key
wg genkey | sudo tee server_private.key
To generate the public key
sudo cat server_private.key | wg pubkey | sudo tee server_public.key
They to display both these keys enter this code
sudo cat server_private.key
sudo cat server_public.key
Save these codes into a safe place that is accessible.
# Using the WireGuard interface
To create a configuring file in your webserver enter this code
sudo nano /etc/wireguard/wg0.conf
add these configuration 
[Interface] 
Address = 10.0.0.1/24 
ListenPort = 51820 
PrivateKey = server_private_key 

SaveConfig = true

Change the server_private_key with your actual key.
# Enabling your IP
Now open your ssh and enter this code
sudo nano /etc/sysctl.conf
find #net.ipv4.ip_forward=1 and remove #
To apply changes enter
sudo sysctl - p
# Starting WireGuard 
To start wireguard on your webserver enter
sudo systemctl enable wg-quick@wg0
sudo systecmctl start wg-quick@wg0
sudo systemctl status wg-quick@wg0
What you should expect to see is active(running)

# Double check VPN interface
To check your interface enter this code
sudo wg 
You should see what you entered in when you intially added the code to your interface.

# Firewall
To config your firewall your going to have to open your virtual machine on mircosoft and then select networking and create an inbound security rule it may already be done but just to make sure put this code in.
Protocol     UDP
Port         51820
Action       allow
These might already be done so if it is leave as is.

# Client configuration 
[Interface]
PrivateKey = client_private_key 
Address = 10.0.0.2/24 
[Peer] 
PublicKey = server_public_key 
Endpoint = your_domain_:51820 
AllowedIPs = 0.0.0.0/0 
PersistentKeepalive = 25
# Checking the IP
Now all you have to do is to ping your ip and check if it replies correctly and everything is working.

